1
00:00:37,100 --> 00:00:41,200
(Touch Your Heart)

2
00:00:41,800 --> 00:00:43,733
(Episode 5)

3
00:01:04,400 --> 00:01:06,833
Who is it so early in the morning?

4
00:01:08,800 --> 00:01:11,566
I'll be seeing a client,
so will be in an hour late.

5
00:01:20,666 --> 00:01:22,620
Alright. I see.

6
00:01:22,700 --> 00:01:23,753
It's going to be cold today,

7
00:01:23,833 --> 00:01:25,733
so make sure to dress warm.

8
00:01:30,666 --> 00:01:32,266
Was that going too far?

9
00:01:33,666 --> 00:01:36,066
Make sure to dress warm too,
Ms. Oh Jin-shim.

10
00:01:47,433 --> 00:01:51,453
Well, he told me to dress warm,

11
00:01:51,533 --> 00:01:53,866
so I'll dress warm, then.

12
00:01:54,466 --> 00:01:56,920
Pink is always right!

13
00:01:57,000 --> 00:01:58,366
I look so pretty.

14
00:02:09,100 --> 00:02:10,753
Doors closing.

15
00:02:10,833 --> 00:02:11,753
Wait! Please wait for me!

16
00:02:11,833 --> 00:02:13,633
Ah, thank you.

17
00:02:15,333 --> 00:02:16,886
Oh, it's you, Kwon.

18
00:02:16,966 --> 00:02:18,700
Doors closing.

19
00:02:19,666 --> 00:02:21,686
As always, I bump into you
in the elevator.

20
00:02:21,766 --> 00:02:24,386
Even though I came in an hour late
as I was seeing a client.

21
00:02:24,466 --> 00:02:27,353
If someone else heard us,
they'll think that

22
00:02:27,433 --> 00:02:30,886
I'm always waiting around the
elevator to bump into you.

23
00:02:30,966 --> 00:02:33,966
I was also seeing a client too,
that's why I came in late.

24
00:02:37,633 --> 00:02:39,553
By the way, I have some good news.

25
00:02:39,633 --> 00:02:41,153
I don't want to know.

26
00:02:41,233 --> 00:02:42,886
Your good news has
never turned out to be

27
00:02:42,966 --> 00:02:45,400
quite good for me.

28
00:02:46,166 --> 00:02:47,553
I mean it this time!

29
00:02:47,633 --> 00:02:51,786
I have two amazingly good news,

30
00:02:51,866 --> 00:02:53,286
so which would you like to
hear first?

31
00:02:53,366 --> 00:02:56,553
There's the big good news,
and the small good news.

32
00:02:56,633 --> 00:02:57,633
Fine.

33
00:02:58,133 --> 00:02:59,686
Since us men always go for big,

34
00:02:59,766 --> 00:03:01,653
I'll tell you the
big good news first.

35
00:03:01,733 --> 00:03:03,486
Always may be

36
00:03:03,566 --> 00:03:05,953
taking on a big, big case.

37
00:03:06,033 --> 00:03:07,553
It's 99% confirmed at the moment,

38
00:03:07,633 --> 00:03:09,053
but if we do take it,

39
00:03:09,133 --> 00:03:11,766
we'll be able to make
a name for ourselves.

40
00:03:12,366 --> 00:03:14,100
Just what is this case anyway?

41
00:03:15,466 --> 00:03:16,866
Oh, that's a secret.

42
00:03:19,200 --> 00:03:21,353
Now the small good news.

43
00:03:21,433 --> 00:03:23,466
We're going to have
a group dinner tonight.

44
00:03:25,266 --> 00:03:26,186
Kwon?

45
00:03:26,266 --> 00:03:28,466
Kwon, where's your answer?

46
00:03:29,166 --> 00:03:30,353
We're going to have
a group dinner tonight.

47
00:03:30,433 --> 00:03:32,420
I won't be there.

48
00:03:32,500 --> 00:03:33,933
You always say that.

49
00:03:35,033 --> 00:03:36,420
Why can't you enjoy even the

50
00:03:36,500 --> 00:03:38,000
good news that's brought to you?

51
00:03:39,466 --> 00:03:41,033
He's a weird one.

52
00:03:42,233 --> 00:03:43,153
Sorry I'm late today.

53
00:03:43,233 --> 00:03:44,400
Ah, you're here.

54
00:03:51,533 --> 00:03:53,486
What's all this?

55
00:03:53,566 --> 00:03:55,553
It's so pretty, right?

56
00:03:55,633 --> 00:03:56,753
Spring is coming.

57
00:03:56,833 --> 00:04:00,520
So I decided to make it
all... Pink pink!

58
00:04:00,600 --> 00:04:02,586
Even if spring is approaching,

59
00:04:02,666 --> 00:04:05,820
"pink pink" for
a law firm, is a bit...

60
00:04:05,900 --> 00:04:06,953
So...?

61
00:04:07,033 --> 00:04:08,266
Are you saying it's not allowed?

62
00:04:09,500 --> 00:04:10,986
You do realize that

63
00:04:11,066 --> 00:04:12,620
that's violating my right to
pursue happiness,

64
00:04:12,700 --> 00:04:15,853
and my freedom of
common action, right?

65
00:04:15,933 --> 00:04:16,953
How did you...

66
00:04:17,033 --> 00:04:19,286
You told me at the
drive-in theater.

67
00:04:19,366 --> 00:04:22,353
I have a good memory,
so I remember everything.

68
00:04:22,433 --> 00:04:24,020
Fine, then.

69
00:04:24,100 --> 00:04:25,500
Do what you want.

70
00:04:37,700 --> 00:04:39,233
What is all this?

71
00:04:41,633 --> 00:04:44,153
It's not nice to just
skip your desk, so...

72
00:04:44,233 --> 00:04:47,453
Still, I prefer black over
"pink pink."

73
00:04:47,533 --> 00:04:49,586
Even if you do prefer black,

74
00:04:49,666 --> 00:04:52,453
why don't you try pink sometimes?

75
00:04:52,533 --> 00:04:53,986
You'll find that it cheers you up.

76
00:04:54,066 --> 00:04:55,353
Please respect my right to
pursue happiness,

77
00:04:55,433 --> 00:04:58,720
and my freedom of
common action as well.

78
00:04:58,800 --> 00:05:01,300
Alright, I'll clear them.

79
00:05:07,966 --> 00:05:09,033
The strawberry...

80
00:05:14,300 --> 00:05:15,300
Oh, um.

81
00:05:16,333 --> 00:05:17,386
Take these, too.

82
00:05:17,466 --> 00:05:19,186
Just keep them.

83
00:05:19,266 --> 00:05:21,353
When I'm away from my desk,

84
00:05:21,433 --> 00:05:23,486
you could just leave
a note for me, can't you?

85
00:05:23,566 --> 00:05:25,453
So that we don't both just
forget about it.

86
00:05:25,533 --> 00:05:26,566
Then please excuse me.

87
00:05:29,133 --> 00:05:30,166
Then...

88
00:05:41,033 --> 00:05:42,166
What the...

89
00:05:47,933 --> 00:05:48,966
Yes.

90
00:05:50,300 --> 00:05:52,853
I'll send that certificate of
contents through, then.

91
00:05:52,933 --> 00:05:53,933
Alright.

92
00:06:14,766 --> 00:06:17,200
(Please send that certificate of
contents to Ms. Jung Da-young)

93
00:06:18,366 --> 00:06:21,333
Please send that certificate of
contents to Ms. Jung Da-young.

94
00:06:23,933 --> 00:06:25,566
(Yes, Mr. Kwon)

95
00:06:28,866 --> 00:06:29,900
Yes?

96
00:06:50,800 --> 00:06:52,433
"Yes, Mr. Kwon."

97
00:06:53,466 --> 00:06:55,033
She could've just said it instead.

98
00:07:05,333 --> 00:07:07,086
Could you submit an application to

99
00:07:07,166 --> 00:07:09,533
change Mr. Park Jae-won's hearing
to next Tuesday?

100
00:07:12,066 --> 00:07:14,853
It's been re-scheduled for
February 26th, at 3 p.m.

101
00:07:14,933 --> 00:07:16,320
Please contact the Prosecution
Service in Cheongju

102
00:07:16,400 --> 00:07:19,666
and ask for Mr. Baek Sun-myung's
case files.

103
00:07:20,400 --> 00:07:22,020
All done.

104
00:07:22,100 --> 00:07:25,586
Please check and inform
Mr. Han of the appellate deadline.

105
00:07:25,666 --> 00:07:27,453
The deadline is the 27th,

106
00:07:27,533 --> 00:07:29,200
and he'd like to appeal.

107
00:07:30,633 --> 00:07:31,720
Thank you.

108
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:33,620
I'm sorry I've been
dumping work on you.

109
00:07:33,700 --> 00:07:37,033
No, it's alright. Anytime.

110
00:07:52,466 --> 00:07:53,486
Yes, hello?

111
00:07:53,566 --> 00:07:55,453
Is this quick delivery?

112
00:07:55,533 --> 00:07:57,633
I'm Dan Mun-hee from Always...

113
00:07:58,366 --> 00:07:59,786
Yes.

114
00:07:59,866 --> 00:08:03,220
I need to send something by
quick delivery.

115
00:08:03,300 --> 00:08:05,733
Alright, I'll be waiting.

116
00:08:12,300 --> 00:08:14,933
I wonder what he thinks of me.

117
00:08:19,100 --> 00:08:21,220
He...

118
00:08:21,300 --> 00:08:22,786
He likes me,

119
00:08:22,866 --> 00:08:24,153
he likes me not.

120
00:08:24,233 --> 00:08:25,586
he likes me,

121
00:08:25,666 --> 00:08:26,620
he likes me not.

122
00:08:26,700 --> 00:08:28,466
He likes me, he likes me not.

123
00:08:30,733 --> 00:08:32,166
- He...
- ...likes me!

124
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:39,733
I guess he must like you, too!

125
00:08:41,133 --> 00:08:43,853
But you know, I've seen
people do it with flower petals,

126
00:08:43,933 --> 00:08:45,786
but never with mandarin oranges.

127
00:08:45,866 --> 00:08:47,220
It's my first time, too.

128
00:08:47,300 --> 00:08:49,600
I'm just so desperate to know
what he thinks of me.

129
00:08:51,466 --> 00:08:52,720
What's he like?

130
00:08:52,800 --> 00:08:55,420
Is it still one-sided?

131
00:08:55,500 --> 00:08:58,053
Well.

132
00:08:58,133 --> 00:09:01,200
I think he's interested
in me, too, and...

133
00:09:02,800 --> 00:09:04,720
Will you hear me out?

134
00:09:04,800 --> 00:09:06,186
Yes, sure.

135
00:09:06,266 --> 00:09:09,220
He's the quick delivery guy
who often comes to our office.

136
00:09:09,300 --> 00:09:10,820
And his tone changes
when he's talking to me.

137
00:09:10,900 --> 00:09:12,986
To other people, he's like,

138
00:09:13,066 --> 00:09:14,453
"Did you call for
delivery service?"

139
00:09:14,533 --> 00:09:16,100
But to me, he's like, "Did you
call for delivery service?"

140
00:09:17,033 --> 00:09:18,986
Just shows how much
he's excited to see me.

141
00:09:19,066 --> 00:09:20,286
But that's not all.

142
00:09:20,366 --> 00:09:22,086
They give you a free keychain

143
00:09:22,166 --> 00:09:23,653
after you use their
service for five times,

144
00:09:23,733 --> 00:09:24,953
but I only called 4 times.
Just four times,

145
00:09:25,033 --> 00:09:26,966
and only four times, yet...!

146
00:09:27,633 --> 00:09:30,020
Yet he gave me this key chain.

147
00:09:30,100 --> 00:09:33,000
Love makes you want to give
everything you have, right?

148
00:09:33,800 --> 00:09:35,986
Wow, that's so pretty.

149
00:09:36,066 --> 00:09:39,953
I guess he's head over
heels in love with you.

150
00:09:40,033 --> 00:09:42,053
- Really?
- Yes.

151
00:09:42,133 --> 00:09:44,353
Since it's coming from you,
who's dated a ton of guys,

152
00:09:44,433 --> 00:09:45,586
I'll believe you.

153
00:09:45,666 --> 00:09:46,586
Huh?

154
00:09:46,666 --> 00:09:48,620
I've never… had a relationship.

155
00:09:48,700 --> 00:09:51,086
Oh, right. I read your interview.

156
00:09:51,166 --> 00:09:52,600
So you've never had a boyfriend.

157
00:09:54,133 --> 00:09:56,620
But even though
I've never been in a relationship,

158
00:09:56,700 --> 00:09:58,286
I'm good at giving advice on love.

159
00:09:58,366 --> 00:09:59,753
Remember that
matchmaking TV show?

160
00:09:59,833 --> 00:10:01,866
I even hosted that show!

161
00:10:03,466 --> 00:10:05,066
So from how I see it,

162
00:10:06,466 --> 00:10:07,886
it's 100%.

163
00:10:07,966 --> 00:10:09,486
Oh please!

164
00:10:09,566 --> 00:10:10,566
Yay!

165
00:10:13,633 --> 00:10:15,266
- This is a secret, alright?
- Sure.

166
00:10:16,566 --> 00:10:17,786
Wow.

167
00:10:17,866 --> 00:10:19,633
She must really like him.

168
00:10:24,166 --> 00:10:25,400
So with mandarins oranges...?

169
00:10:26,533 --> 00:10:29,233
Should I try it too, then?

170
00:10:42,933 --> 00:10:44,233
He likes me,

171
00:10:44,666 --> 00:10:46,233
he likes me not.

172
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:48,966
He likes me,

173
00:10:51,966 --> 00:10:53,800
he likes me not.

174
00:10:54,466 --> 00:10:55,486
(He likes me
He likes me not)

175
00:10:55,566 --> 00:10:57,033
(He likes me
He likes me...)

176
00:10:59,933 --> 00:11:01,166
He likes me!

177
00:11:06,966 --> 00:11:09,053
Ms. Oh Jin-shim,
it's time to go to Court.

178
00:11:09,133 --> 00:11:11,366
Yes, I'm coming.

179
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:16,420
Our witness' testimony just now

180
00:11:16,500 --> 00:11:17,820
validates my client's alibi as true.

181
00:11:17,900 --> 00:11:21,153
In other words, he was not
present at the scene.

182
00:11:21,233 --> 00:11:23,486
So Your Honor,

183
00:11:23,566 --> 00:11:25,466
I ask that you sentence him
not guilty.

184
00:11:36,300 --> 00:11:37,520
Mr. Kwon.

185
00:11:37,600 --> 00:11:39,520
It looks like we'll win, right?

186
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:40,986
Yes, well...

187
00:11:41,066 --> 00:11:43,220
No need to be so humble!

188
00:11:43,300 --> 00:11:47,153
You're smiling, so that means
you're confident that we will.

189
00:11:47,233 --> 00:11:49,933
I guess you're a lawyer,
being happy over a win.

190
00:11:52,733 --> 00:11:56,466
By the way, why did you
decide to become a lawyer?

191
00:11:59,900 --> 00:12:00,920
From what I heard,

192
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:04,220
I heard all your friends from
college are now prosecutors.

193
00:12:04,300 --> 00:12:06,566
Lawyers make much more money.

194
00:12:10,066 --> 00:12:12,920
Oh what? He became
a lawyer for money?

195
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:15,453
So he's honest too, isn't he?

196
00:12:15,533 --> 00:12:17,766
The more you get to know him,
the more charming he is.

197
00:12:23,800 --> 00:12:25,186
It's lunchtime,

198
00:12:25,266 --> 00:12:27,200
so should we have lunch
before going back in?

199
00:12:27,633 --> 00:12:28,733
Sure.

200
00:12:34,100 --> 00:12:35,486
Oh what?

201
00:12:35,566 --> 00:12:36,600
Ah, that's right.

202
00:12:38,933 --> 00:12:40,686
What if she asks us to
join her for coffee again?

203
00:12:40,766 --> 00:12:41,720
No.

204
00:12:41,800 --> 00:12:44,833
Since it's lunchtime, she might
ask us to go for lunch.

205
00:12:46,666 --> 00:12:47,733
Aren't you coming?

206
00:12:49,766 --> 00:12:51,186
I am. Let's go!

207
00:12:51,266 --> 00:12:53,033
Come on, hurry up!

208
00:12:55,266 --> 00:12:57,020
- Kwon Jung-rok!
- Huh?

209
00:12:57,100 --> 00:12:58,386
UFO!

210
00:12:58,466 --> 00:12:59,653
- What?
- Over there!

211
00:12:59,733 --> 00:13:00,653
It went over there.

212
00:13:00,733 --> 00:13:02,786
Come on, hurry up!

213
00:13:02,866 --> 00:13:04,233
- Hurry up!
- Jung-rok.

214
00:13:05,300 --> 00:13:06,353
Hey.

215
00:13:06,433 --> 00:13:07,853
I guess you had a trial?

216
00:13:07,933 --> 00:13:08,933
Yes.

217
00:13:09,633 --> 00:13:10,853
I'm bumping into you
quite often, aren't I?

218
00:13:10,933 --> 00:13:12,366
What, you don't like that?

219
00:13:13,266 --> 00:13:15,720
Hello, so you came with him
today, Ms. Oh.

220
00:13:15,800 --> 00:13:16,886
Yes, well...

221
00:13:16,966 --> 00:13:18,620
If you're alright for time,
how about we go for lunch?

222
00:13:18,700 --> 00:13:20,420
How does pasta sound?

223
00:13:20,500 --> 00:13:21,953
Pasta?

224
00:13:22,033 --> 00:13:24,800
You see, there's something
I want to talk to you about.

225
00:13:27,266 --> 00:13:28,820
- Is it something important?
- Yes.

226
00:13:28,900 --> 00:13:30,220
It's very important.

227
00:13:30,300 --> 00:13:32,566
And quite confidential, too.

228
00:13:34,633 --> 00:13:36,900
I'm very sorry, but
please go ahead first.

229
00:13:37,900 --> 00:13:38,900
What?

230
00:13:44,033 --> 00:13:45,386
Go ahead first?

231
00:13:45,466 --> 00:13:46,820
He promised to go have
lunch with him first,

232
00:13:46,900 --> 00:13:47,986
so why won't he keep his promise?

233
00:13:48,066 --> 00:13:49,700
Doesn't he know
just how much I like...

234
00:13:51,133 --> 00:13:52,366
...pasta?

235
00:13:57,066 --> 00:14:00,133
So, what's this important and
confidential subject?

236
00:14:02,700 --> 00:14:04,986
- You know the Lim Yun-hee case?
- Yes.

237
00:14:05,066 --> 00:14:07,986
I've been put in charge of it.

238
00:14:08,066 --> 00:14:11,120
Here we have a woman who's
a long-time DV victim,

239
00:14:11,200 --> 00:14:14,353
and she stabbed her husband to
death when he beat her up.

240
00:14:14,433 --> 00:14:16,586
So, is this homicide or
self-defense?

241
00:14:16,666 --> 00:14:18,033
What are your thoughts?

242
00:14:19,600 --> 00:14:21,886
But if her claim of
self-defense is accepted,

243
00:14:21,966 --> 00:14:24,953
not only is it a burden for the
prosecutor leading the

244
00:14:25,033 --> 00:14:26,220
investigation, but many more
people in a similar situation

245
00:14:26,300 --> 00:14:28,620
will claim self-defense
in the future.

246
00:14:28,700 --> 00:14:30,653
And all the lawyers too,
will take this as an example

247
00:14:30,733 --> 00:14:32,466
and argue for
self-defense as well.

248
00:14:33,733 --> 00:14:35,566
As you can see, it's
a sensitive topic for us.

249
00:14:37,933 --> 00:14:40,653
But this is a grey zone.

250
00:14:40,733 --> 00:14:41,800
Right?

251
00:14:43,933 --> 00:14:46,186
I wasn't asking you,
hoping for an answer.

252
00:14:46,266 --> 00:14:49,853
I just took the case, pretending
I'm ready to handle it,

253
00:14:49,933 --> 00:14:51,300
but really, I'm quite lost.

254
00:14:59,300 --> 00:15:00,733
Shall we go get coffee?

255
00:15:02,166 --> 00:15:03,920
No, I have to get going.

256
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:06,420
Why? I thought
you still had some time left.

257
00:15:06,500 --> 00:15:08,566
I have something to do.
I'll catch you later, then.

258
00:15:11,100 --> 00:15:12,733
Why's he so busy?

259
00:15:21,866 --> 00:15:22,986
Why were you in there?

260
00:15:23,066 --> 00:15:24,753
To confiscate these!

261
00:15:24,833 --> 00:15:29,053
You're not qualified to
have these notes.

262
00:15:29,133 --> 00:15:31,220
Do I need to be? For notes?

263
00:15:31,300 --> 00:15:33,753
Why? I thought you didn't
want them from the start.

264
00:15:33,833 --> 00:15:35,853
Now you want them, do you?

265
00:15:35,933 --> 00:15:38,253
Not quite, but why take back
something you gave to me?

266
00:15:38,333 --> 00:15:39,953
Because I want to.
These were mine anyway.

267
00:15:40,033 --> 00:15:41,920
If that ticks you off,
then sue me.

268
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:43,853
I don't think that's necessary.

269
00:15:43,933 --> 00:15:45,686
There's still 20 minutes to go,

270
00:15:45,766 --> 00:15:46,920
so why don't we go out
so you can eat lunch?

271
00:15:47,000 --> 00:15:48,933
I'm not in the mood for
lunch anymore!

272
00:15:52,900 --> 00:15:55,353
Why are you glaring at me?

273
00:15:55,433 --> 00:15:56,453
I'm not.

274
00:15:56,533 --> 00:15:59,186
People always tell me my
eyes always burn with intensity.

275
00:15:59,266 --> 00:16:00,186
But to be an actress,

276
00:16:00,266 --> 00:16:02,966
you need to be able to knock back
the camera with your eyes.

277
00:16:11,766 --> 00:16:13,686
Alright, then. Have a nice one.

278
00:16:13,766 --> 00:16:14,766
Um, excuse me.

279
00:16:15,633 --> 00:16:16,586
Yes?

280
00:16:16,666 --> 00:16:18,853
Did you have something to say?

281
00:16:18,933 --> 00:16:22,220
This is totally out of the blue,
but let's have lunch sometime.

282
00:16:22,300 --> 00:16:24,053
- Sorry?
- How about tomorrow?

283
00:16:24,133 --> 00:16:26,453
Why don't we go somewhere
nice together for lunch?

284
00:16:26,533 --> 00:16:30,186
Oh... I don't think I'll be
all that hungry tomorrow.

285
00:16:30,266 --> 00:16:31,420
Then let's watch a movie!

286
00:16:31,500 --> 00:16:33,920
Do you like melodramas?
How about "Love in Titicaca?"

287
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:35,653
- How does that sound?
- I watched it yesterday.

288
00:16:35,733 --> 00:16:37,033
It comes out tomorrow.

289
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:39,653
Oh... So it comes out tomorrow.

290
00:16:39,733 --> 00:16:43,986
Um, I'll just be direct.

291
00:16:44,066 --> 00:16:45,833
I like you too, Chan-seong.

292
00:16:46,200 --> 00:16:47,200
"I like you too?"

293
00:16:48,200 --> 00:16:51,153
So I'd like to
see a movie with you

294
00:16:51,233 --> 00:16:52,720
or have lunch with you,

295
00:16:52,800 --> 00:16:55,166
so that I can get to
know you better.

296
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:02,220
Sorry, but I really
didn't see this coming.

297
00:17:02,300 --> 00:17:06,486
Will you give me
some time to think?

298
00:17:06,566 --> 00:17:08,986
Of course.

299
00:17:09,066 --> 00:17:09,986
But how much time?

300
00:17:10,066 --> 00:17:11,453
About...

301
00:17:11,533 --> 00:17:12,566
...ten years?

302
00:17:14,300 --> 00:17:15,366
Take care, then.

303
00:17:21,233 --> 00:17:23,320
I'm off to see a client, and
will go straight home from there.

304
00:17:23,400 --> 00:17:24,400
Alright.

305
00:17:26,166 --> 00:17:29,420
Are you mad at me for something?

306
00:17:29,500 --> 00:17:31,920
If this is about
how I broke our promise to

307
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:34,453
have lunch together earlier...

308
00:17:34,533 --> 00:17:36,986
It's nothing like that.

309
00:17:37,066 --> 00:17:38,186
Then why are you...

310
00:17:38,266 --> 00:17:40,586
Do I have to tell you everything?

311
00:17:40,666 --> 00:17:44,586
Don't you know we have
the right to privacy?

312
00:17:44,666 --> 00:17:46,520
Did I teach you this, too?

313
00:17:46,600 --> 00:17:48,220
No, I learned that on my own.

314
00:17:48,300 --> 00:17:50,166
It's stated in Article 17,
of our Constitution.

315
00:17:53,033 --> 00:17:55,166
But that's not
what's important here.

316
00:17:56,966 --> 00:17:57,886
Alright, then.

317
00:17:57,966 --> 00:18:00,366
I'll respect
your right to privacy.

318
00:18:01,866 --> 00:18:02,866
Um...

319
00:18:05,066 --> 00:18:06,500
Can I ask you something?

320
00:18:08,000 --> 00:18:10,286
Between "Avatar"
you watched in 2009,

321
00:18:10,366 --> 00:18:13,320
and "What's Wrong With
My Lawyer" you watched last week,

322
00:18:13,400 --> 00:18:16,153
which did you like better?

323
00:18:16,233 --> 00:18:17,486
Sorry?

324
00:18:17,566 --> 00:18:19,286
I'm asking,
which you liked better,

325
00:18:19,366 --> 00:18:21,466
and which was more memorable.

326
00:18:23,400 --> 00:18:27,086
"Avatar" dealt with a unique theme
so it was entertaining,

327
00:18:27,166 --> 00:18:28,886
but so was
"What's Wrong With My Lawyer,"

328
00:18:28,966 --> 00:18:30,233
because I could relate to it.

329
00:18:32,333 --> 00:18:35,353
So you like both,

330
00:18:35,433 --> 00:18:37,720
and can't choose between the two?

331
00:18:37,800 --> 00:18:40,300
You're really bad, you know that?

332
00:18:52,366 --> 00:18:54,020
Then I'll see you on the
day of the trial.

333
00:18:54,100 --> 00:18:57,453
Sure, please tell me if you need
any more documents.

334
00:18:57,533 --> 00:18:59,166
- I'll see you, then.
- Goodbye.

335
00:19:04,466 --> 00:19:07,120
Please re-check with
our witness that

336
00:19:07,200 --> 00:19:08,653
he'll be standing in Court
next week,

337
00:19:08,733 --> 00:19:10,366
and guide him through
the procedures.

338
00:19:19,733 --> 00:19:21,333
(OK)

339
00:19:21,566 --> 00:19:23,133
"OK?"

340
00:19:27,466 --> 00:19:29,033
What's wrong with her?

341
00:19:39,466 --> 00:19:40,853
Welcome.

342
00:19:40,933 --> 00:19:42,900
Should I have booked
a private room?

343
00:19:43,700 --> 00:19:44,620
Yun-seo,

344
00:19:44,700 --> 00:19:48,020
are you fine with having dinner
in an open space?

345
00:19:48,100 --> 00:19:49,120
Sure.

346
00:19:49,200 --> 00:19:51,000
I'll just sit in a corner,
like this.

347
00:19:51,533 --> 00:19:53,900
Mr. Kwon's not joining us
again, is he?

348
00:19:54,766 --> 00:19:58,320
Have you ever seen Kwon
join us on his free will?

349
00:19:58,400 --> 00:20:00,086
Hey, over there!

350
00:20:00,166 --> 00:20:02,466
He's joined us on
his free will tonight.

351
00:20:11,800 --> 00:20:13,020
- Alright, cheers!
- Cheers!

352
00:20:13,100 --> 00:20:15,300
We've the whole team here
in a long time.

353
00:20:20,733 --> 00:20:23,286
Ms. Dan, why are you
drinking like that?

354
00:20:23,366 --> 00:20:24,920
She's been rejected again.

355
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:27,220
By that quick delivery guy
this time.

356
00:20:27,300 --> 00:20:28,786
- Really?
- Wow.

357
00:20:28,866 --> 00:20:30,386
You were quick to fall for him

358
00:20:30,466 --> 00:20:32,753
and to be rejected, weren't you?

359
00:20:32,833 --> 00:20:34,020
You must be quite busy, Ms. Dan.

360
00:20:34,100 --> 00:20:37,766
Being rejected at least
once a week!

361
00:20:39,800 --> 00:20:41,033
What did you say?

362
00:20:46,000 --> 00:20:47,153
Anyway, what happened?

363
00:20:47,233 --> 00:20:48,953
You said you won't be coming,
just this morning.

364
00:20:49,033 --> 00:20:50,986
What changed your mind?

365
00:20:51,066 --> 00:20:52,100
Well...

366
00:20:54,700 --> 00:20:56,820
Why are you looking at Yun-seo?

367
00:20:56,900 --> 00:20:59,920
Are you here to see Yun-seo?

368
00:21:00,000 --> 00:21:03,853
Yes. I'm here to see
Ms. Oh Jin-shim.

369
00:21:03,933 --> 00:21:05,920
Whoa, he straight up admitted it!

370
00:21:06,000 --> 00:21:08,086
Then something's going on
between you two, is there?

371
00:21:08,166 --> 00:21:09,620
What?

372
00:21:09,700 --> 00:21:11,553
That's just preposterous.

373
00:21:11,633 --> 00:21:13,420
- It's not like that.
- Then...

374
00:21:13,500 --> 00:21:15,586
...why that shocking statement?

375
00:21:15,666 --> 00:21:16,853
It's nothing shocking.

376
00:21:16,933 --> 00:21:19,066
I'm really here to see
Ms. Oh Jin-shim.

377
00:21:20,366 --> 00:21:21,353
I had something to ask her.

378
00:21:21,433 --> 00:21:23,153
Something to ask her?

379
00:21:23,233 --> 00:21:24,653
She's been working diligently,

380
00:21:24,733 --> 00:21:26,153
and very enthusiastic
about her work too,

381
00:21:26,233 --> 00:21:27,520
even using her own time to
study law.

382
00:21:27,600 --> 00:21:30,420
But today, for some reason,
she was half-hearted in her duties

383
00:21:30,500 --> 00:21:33,153
and expressed her
discontent with me.

384
00:21:33,233 --> 00:21:35,020
I know she's not someone to
do that without a reason,

385
00:21:35,100 --> 00:21:36,986
so I came here to
clear any misunderstanding.

386
00:21:37,066 --> 00:21:38,120
Ms. Oh Jin-shim.

387
00:21:38,200 --> 00:21:40,166
Just why are you mad at me?

388
00:21:43,766 --> 00:21:47,220
What... You're asking,
in front of everyone?

389
00:21:47,300 --> 00:21:50,120
Yes. I thought I should
so others can hear us out.

390
00:21:50,200 --> 00:21:52,186
And if the majority judges
it was my fault,

391
00:21:52,266 --> 00:21:54,186
I'll try and fix my faults.

392
00:21:54,266 --> 00:21:57,000
So please. Go ahead and tell me.

393
00:22:03,700 --> 00:22:05,053
You said it wasn't because

394
00:22:05,133 --> 00:22:07,233
I couldn't keep my promise
that I'll have lunch with you.

395
00:22:08,100 --> 00:22:10,520
Then is it perhaps because

396
00:22:10,600 --> 00:22:12,720
I forbid you from decorating
my office in pink?

397
00:22:12,800 --> 00:22:14,253
- Excuse me, Mr. Kwon.
- What...

398
00:22:14,333 --> 00:22:15,633
What's this about?

399
00:22:16,900 --> 00:22:20,400
Um, you see... I like pink.

400
00:22:21,666 --> 00:22:22,833
I really do.

401
00:22:23,700 --> 00:22:25,320
So uh...

402
00:22:25,400 --> 00:22:28,486
I decorated
Mr. Kwon's office in pink,

403
00:22:28,566 --> 00:22:30,853
and he said he hates it. And I...

404
00:22:30,933 --> 00:22:33,220
But that's not why I'm mad.

405
00:22:33,300 --> 00:22:35,820
Then are you mad because

406
00:22:35,900 --> 00:22:37,120
I gave you so much work today?

407
00:22:37,200 --> 00:22:39,520
Because I kept sticking notes
on your desk?

408
00:22:39,600 --> 00:22:43,453
Tsk, you've no humanity, do you?

409
00:22:43,533 --> 00:22:46,453
If you have work to give her,
ask her politely in person,

410
00:22:46,533 --> 00:22:48,453
instead of just chucking
notes on her desk!

411
00:22:48,533 --> 00:22:50,720
Even I'd be offended. Right?

412
00:22:50,800 --> 00:22:52,686
No, it's not because of that.

413
00:22:52,766 --> 00:22:53,766
It's uh...

414
00:22:55,166 --> 00:22:59,366
Well, I don't think I had
a particular reason, really.

415
00:23:01,733 --> 00:23:03,720
I think I was just...

416
00:23:03,800 --> 00:23:06,800
...all sensitive, because
I was hungry.

417
00:23:09,600 --> 00:23:11,200
Yes, right.

418
00:23:17,700 --> 00:23:23,086
I'm sorry I made you
misunderstand, Mr. Kwon.

419
00:23:23,166 --> 00:23:24,353
It's alright.

420
00:23:24,433 --> 00:23:26,300
I'm glad that's been cleared up.

421
00:23:27,066 --> 00:23:28,920
So it was nothing after all.

422
00:23:29,000 --> 00:23:30,966
Then why don't we
drink to your making up?

423
00:23:31,533 --> 00:23:33,666
No, there's no need.

424
00:23:38,800 --> 00:23:41,620
I guess Mr. Kwon feels much better
now that it's been cleared.

425
00:23:41,700 --> 00:23:42,766
Come on.

426
00:23:45,466 --> 00:23:46,600
Cheers!

427
00:23:49,766 --> 00:23:50,833
That's nice to see.

428
00:23:55,566 --> 00:23:56,600
Please, go on.

429
00:23:57,400 --> 00:23:58,433
Sure.

430
00:24:15,300 --> 00:24:16,733
Mr. Kwon?

431
00:24:17,466 --> 00:24:20,200
Can I talk to you?

432
00:24:21,400 --> 00:24:22,433
Sure.

433
00:24:23,933 --> 00:24:26,053
I thought we cleared
our misunderstandings.

434
00:24:26,133 --> 00:24:27,700
So what's this about now?

435
00:24:29,766 --> 00:24:31,653
Why did you?

436
00:24:31,733 --> 00:24:34,520
Why did you do that?

437
00:24:34,600 --> 00:24:35,553
- Why did I... What?
- It's...

438
00:24:35,633 --> 00:24:37,986
This is about us,

439
00:24:38,066 --> 00:24:40,320
so we should solve it between us.

440
00:24:40,400 --> 00:24:42,186
So why did you have to go and

441
00:24:42,266 --> 00:24:44,753
blab about it, in front of
everyone else? Why?

442
00:24:44,833 --> 00:24:46,286
Blab about it?

443
00:24:46,366 --> 00:24:47,420
As I explained before,

444
00:24:47,500 --> 00:24:49,886
I wanted everyone to
hear me out, and

445
00:24:49,966 --> 00:24:51,700
if the majority judged that
it was my fault...

446
00:24:52,633 --> 00:24:54,886
What, is this a trial?

447
00:24:54,966 --> 00:24:57,453
Picking faults in front of
everyone, that's...

448
00:24:57,533 --> 00:24:58,933
How's that different to a trial?

449
00:25:01,400 --> 00:25:03,353
I'm sorry if that offended you.

450
00:25:03,433 --> 00:25:05,720
But now that we finally
cleared our misunderstanding...

451
00:25:05,800 --> 00:25:09,620
Clear our misunderstanding?
Whatever!

452
00:25:09,700 --> 00:25:12,220
Oh no, we're not done yet.

453
00:25:12,300 --> 00:25:13,753
Why?

454
00:25:13,833 --> 00:25:17,266
Because the reason
why I'm mad at you, is...

455
00:25:19,566 --> 00:25:21,200
...entirely something else.

456
00:25:22,366 --> 00:25:23,600
Just what...

457
00:25:27,800 --> 00:25:30,633
Why did you go have pasta
with her?

458
00:25:32,133 --> 00:25:33,853
Why not me?

459
00:25:33,933 --> 00:25:35,800
I wanted pasta, too!

460
00:25:38,366 --> 00:25:40,820
Then you were mad at me
for the whole day...

461
00:25:40,900 --> 00:25:43,220
...over pasta?

462
00:25:43,300 --> 00:25:44,853
Let's go get pasta tomorrow, then.

463
00:25:44,933 --> 00:25:47,153
Why did you?

464
00:25:47,233 --> 00:25:52,066
Why did you have pasta
with someone else?

465
00:25:55,000 --> 00:25:56,800
I hate that.

466
00:25:58,233 --> 00:26:00,100
Pasta...

467
00:26:03,966 --> 00:26:06,586
Pasta!

468
00:26:06,666 --> 00:26:08,266
I wanted pasta, too...

469
00:26:18,700 --> 00:26:20,120
Welcome home.

470
00:26:20,200 --> 00:26:21,220
Sure.

471
00:26:21,300 --> 00:26:23,653
By the way, Ju-won told me.

472
00:26:23,733 --> 00:26:25,666
He saw you having pasta
with Yeo-reum.

473
00:26:27,466 --> 00:26:28,453
Pasta again?

474
00:26:28,533 --> 00:26:29,886
What do you mean, again?

475
00:26:29,966 --> 00:26:31,286
This is the first time
I'm asking you about it.

476
00:26:31,366 --> 00:26:32,920
So what? What if I had pasta?

477
00:26:33,000 --> 00:26:34,120
What about it, huh?

478
00:26:34,200 --> 00:26:35,833
I'm saying, I'm jealous.

479
00:26:36,900 --> 00:26:38,186
What?

480
00:26:38,266 --> 00:26:39,920
- Jealous?
- Of course.

481
00:26:40,000 --> 00:26:42,120
Though I'm like this now
after breaking up with her,

482
00:26:42,200 --> 00:26:43,886
that doesn't mean
I'm completely over her.

483
00:26:43,966 --> 00:26:44,920
What, you don't think
I'll be mad when I hear that

484
00:26:45,000 --> 00:26:46,920
the girl I'm interested in is

485
00:26:47,000 --> 00:26:48,300
having pasta with another man?

486
00:26:52,166 --> 00:26:54,686
If you're mad that she had
pasta with someone else...

487
00:26:54,766 --> 00:26:56,453
Does that mean...

488
00:26:56,533 --> 00:26:58,520
...you're interested in her?

489
00:26:58,600 --> 00:26:59,600
What?

490
00:27:11,300 --> 00:27:13,733
She's interested in me?

491
00:27:24,433 --> 00:27:26,320
Hyuk-jun.

492
00:27:26,400 --> 00:27:29,253
Shall we go for a drive
to the sea?

493
00:27:29,333 --> 00:27:31,653
What are you on about
from so early in the morning?

494
00:27:31,733 --> 00:27:34,153
You need to go to work.

495
00:27:34,233 --> 00:27:35,486
Right?

496
00:27:35,566 --> 00:27:37,620
I need to go to work...

497
00:27:37,700 --> 00:27:40,933
Did you do something
stupid again, drunk last night?

498
00:27:42,433 --> 00:27:45,386
Who do you think invented alcohol?

499
00:27:45,466 --> 00:27:47,166
So you did. Yep!

500
00:27:47,966 --> 00:27:48,886
I want to ask myself, too.

501
00:27:48,966 --> 00:27:50,620
Just who invented alcohol,

502
00:27:50,700 --> 00:27:53,453
only to drive you into
a corner, each time?

503
00:27:53,533 --> 00:27:56,053
So what did you do this time?

504
00:27:56,133 --> 00:27:58,120
- I don't know.
- Whatever, tell me!

505
00:27:58,200 --> 00:27:59,686
That way, I can cover up for you

506
00:27:59,766 --> 00:28:01,020
or make excuses for you.

507
00:28:01,100 --> 00:28:02,353
I said, I don't know!

508
00:28:02,433 --> 00:28:04,200
I want to be alone. Get out!

509
00:28:05,766 --> 00:28:07,233
What, here?

510
00:28:10,466 --> 00:28:12,120
We're here now.

511
00:28:12,200 --> 00:28:13,120
Really?

512
00:28:13,200 --> 00:28:14,333
We're here already?

513
00:28:18,800 --> 00:28:20,786
Oh no.

514
00:28:20,866 --> 00:28:23,020
How do I explain myself?

515
00:28:23,100 --> 00:28:24,933
What do I do?

516
00:28:28,100 --> 00:28:29,520
Hello.

517
00:28:29,600 --> 00:28:31,800
Yes, good morning.

518
00:28:43,200 --> 00:28:44,366
Ms. Oh Jin-shim.

519
00:28:48,600 --> 00:28:49,520
Yes?

520
00:28:49,600 --> 00:28:51,120
The trial from yesterday.

521
00:28:51,200 --> 00:28:53,286
Can you check that the
written ruling was sent,

522
00:28:53,366 --> 00:28:55,753
and whether the case 2018-327

523
00:28:55,833 --> 00:28:58,186
has been filed for appeal?

524
00:28:58,266 --> 00:29:00,033
Ah, sure.

525
00:29:02,166 --> 00:29:03,786
Um...

526
00:29:03,866 --> 00:29:05,066
Mr. Kwon?

527
00:29:07,933 --> 00:29:10,433
About what I said last night...

528
00:29:11,300 --> 00:29:13,300
Huh? Just what...

529
