grounds of self-defense.

1045
00:57:50,466 --> 00:57:53,720
At the time, Ms. Lim had
no other intention

1046
00:57:53,800 --> 00:57:56,353
or no other plan whatsoever,

1047
00:57:56,433 --> 00:57:59,900
except for her desperate
will to survive.

1048
00:58:02,566 --> 00:58:06,653
Ms. Lim. You said your mother
walked out on you

1049
00:58:06,733 --> 00:58:08,133
when you were ten.
What was the reason?

1050
00:58:09,500 --> 00:58:12,186
She hit her head hard on the floor

1051
00:58:12,266 --> 00:58:14,553
while being beaten by
my drunk father.

1052
00:58:14,633 --> 00:58:17,386
There was a lot of blood,

1053
00:58:17,466 --> 00:58:21,053
and while father was searching for
something to hit her again with,

1054
00:58:21,133 --> 00:58:22,600
she fled.

1055
00:58:24,233 --> 00:58:26,166
Probably to live.

1056
00:58:34,700 --> 00:58:36,353
And ever since then,

1057
00:58:36,433 --> 00:58:39,820
your father started
abusing you as well.

1058
00:58:39,900 --> 00:58:42,020
Is this true?

1059
00:58:42,100 --> 00:58:44,400
Yes, it's true.

1060
00:58:45,800 --> 00:58:48,120
Your ex-husband, and
Mr. Kim Hyung-tae too,

1061
00:58:48,200 --> 00:58:51,453
were also abusive.

1062
00:58:51,533 --> 00:58:53,953
The memories of your father
must have been painful enough,

1063
00:58:54,033 --> 00:58:56,053
so why did you marry men

1064
00:58:56,133 --> 00:58:58,766
who had the same
violent character?

1065
00:59:03,400 --> 00:59:04,320
Your Honor.

1066
00:59:04,400 --> 00:59:06,553
I'd like to call
her psychologist to stand,

1067
00:59:06,633 --> 00:59:09,400
who may better help us
grasp her situation.

1068
00:59:09,966 --> 00:59:12,886
Though you may be
so convinced at first,

1069
00:59:12,966 --> 00:59:15,420
but when you're exposed to
an abnormal situation for long,

1070
00:59:15,500 --> 00:59:17,686
you come to accept that
this is the norm.

1071
00:59:17,766 --> 00:59:20,120
Could you expand on that?

1072
00:59:20,200 --> 00:59:22,520
Those who have been
abused since young

1073
00:59:22,600 --> 00:59:26,120
fail to realize that abuse is
something that's wrong.

1074
00:59:26,200 --> 00:59:28,620
And at one point, they come to
accept that this is the norm,

1075
00:59:28,700 --> 00:59:30,920
and even find themselves
psychologically unstable

1076
00:59:31,000 --> 00:59:32,920
if this abnormal environment
doesn't hold up.

1077
00:59:33,000 --> 00:59:35,333
In the end, you're left with
a vicious cycle.

1078
00:59:35,866 --> 00:59:39,566
If you look at
our psychologist's report,

1079
00:59:40,633 --> 00:59:42,653
it reads, "Based on the fact
that the patient has been

1080
00:59:42,733 --> 00:59:45,753
exposed to an abusive environment
since childhood,

1081
00:59:45,833 --> 00:59:49,333
it can be said her sense of
judgment is distorted."

1082
00:59:50,600 --> 00:59:53,053
Is this true?

1083
00:59:53,133 --> 00:59:54,820
Yes, that was my conclusion.

1084
00:59:54,900 --> 00:59:57,320
In other words,
according to your analysis,

1085
00:59:57,400 --> 01:00:00,253
we can conclude Ms. Lim was not
mentally sound

1086
01:00:00,333 --> 01:00:02,820
at the time of the incident.

1087
01:00:02,900 --> 01:00:04,933
Do you agree?

1088
01:00:05,933 --> 01:00:06,933
Yes.

1089
01:00:08,500 --> 01:00:09,633
I rest my case.

1090
01:00:12,500 --> 01:00:13,720
Counsel,

1091
01:00:13,800 --> 01:00:15,320
will you cross-examine?

1092
01:00:15,400 --> 01:00:16,400
Yes.

1093
01:00:17,200 --> 01:00:19,053
Ms. Lim Yun-hee.

1094
01:00:19,133 --> 01:00:21,886
These are the applications for
the insurance payouts

1095
01:00:21,966 --> 01:00:25,933
for your ex-husband, and
also for your father's death.

1096
01:00:30,033 --> 01:00:33,153
Did you submit these
papers in person?

1097
01:00:33,233 --> 01:00:34,720
Yes, I did.

1098
01:00:34,800 --> 01:00:38,553
You were also aware that
Mr. Kim Hyung-tae had

1099
01:00:38,633 --> 01:00:40,753
- life insurance?
- Yes.

1100
01:00:40,833 --> 01:00:43,153
Do you know how much
the amount is, in total?

1101
01:00:43,233 --> 01:00:44,453
No, I do not.

1102
01:00:44,533 --> 01:00:48,786
The total payout of the insurance
plan for Mr. Kim is...

1103
01:00:48,866 --> 01:00:51,100
...4.94 million dollars.

1104
01:00:58,000 --> 01:01:01,200
Isn't the amount too large to
simply say you did not know?

1105
01:01:05,933 --> 01:01:07,133
I rest my case.

1106
01:01:14,266 --> 01:01:16,020
Going with abnormality of
mental functioning, are you?

1107
01:01:16,100 --> 01:01:19,820
But then again, even if
self-defense is not accepted,

1108
01:01:19,900 --> 01:01:22,486
it's not bad business for you
if you can reduce her sentence

1109
01:01:22,566 --> 01:01:24,653
by claiming she isn't
mentally sound.

1110
01:01:24,733 --> 01:01:26,000
Don't put it like that.

1111
01:01:27,400 --> 01:01:29,753
Whether it's self defense or
poor mental functioning,

1112
01:01:29,833 --> 01:01:33,320
they're both valid reasons
under the Penal Code.

1113
01:01:33,400 --> 01:01:36,520
I won't ever let the
Court accept your argument,

1114
01:01:36,600 --> 01:01:38,286
so don't even try.

1115
01:01:38,366 --> 01:01:39,453
Because this is

1116
01:01:39,533 --> 01:01:41,700
something you can't win.

1117
01:01:58,466 --> 01:02:00,700
Why are you so hung upon
that Lim Yun-hee case?

1118
01:02:02,066 --> 01:02:04,133
Because this is the only way.

1119
01:02:07,400 --> 01:02:09,586
Though you'll never understand,

1120
01:02:09,666 --> 01:02:11,566
since your starting line was
so far ahead.

1121
01:02:21,666 --> 01:02:22,853
You're back.

1122
01:02:22,933 --> 01:02:24,786
- Welcome back.
- We're back.

1123
01:02:24,866 --> 01:02:26,020
Um...

1124
01:02:26,100 --> 01:02:27,433
What about Mr. Kwon?

1125
01:02:29,466 --> 01:02:32,020
He told me to go ahead first,

1126
01:02:32,100 --> 01:02:33,886
because he needs to speak
with the prosecutor.

1127
01:02:33,966 --> 01:02:35,520
How did the trial go today?

1128
01:02:35,600 --> 01:02:37,153
It's all over the news!

1129
01:02:37,233 --> 01:02:39,286
From your expression...

1130
01:02:39,366 --> 01:02:41,300
Does that mean it didn't go
so favorably for us?

1131
01:02:42,233 --> 01:02:44,320
No. It was all fine

1132
01:02:44,400 --> 01:02:47,086
when Mr. Kwon argued that

1133
01:02:47,166 --> 01:02:49,053
she was not mentally healthy,

1134
01:02:49,133 --> 01:02:53,520
but when the topic of
insurance came up,

1135
01:02:53,600 --> 01:02:56,220
everyone was bought.

1136
01:02:56,300 --> 01:02:59,086
How much is the payout anyway?

1137
01:02:59,166 --> 01:03:01,000
4.9 million dollars.

1138
01:03:01,833 --> 01:03:03,620
4.9 million...

1139
01:03:03,700 --> 01:03:05,386
No wonder the
audience was convinced.

1140
01:03:05,466 --> 01:03:06,386
Right.

1141
01:03:06,466 --> 01:03:08,153
Even I'm starting to suspect that

1142
01:03:08,233 --> 01:03:10,720
she did it for the money.

1143
01:03:10,800 --> 01:03:12,753
Poor Mr. Kwon!

1144
01:03:12,833 --> 01:03:15,786
The media is following
this case closely,

1145
01:03:15,866 --> 01:03:18,820
so if he loses,
that'll mean a lot of damage.

1146
01:03:18,900 --> 01:03:20,553
The ruling's not out yet,

1147
01:03:20,633 --> 01:03:22,786
so don't say that.

1148
01:03:22,866 --> 01:03:24,266
Mr. Kwon...

1149
01:03:26,233 --> 01:03:27,466
I'm back.

1150
01:03:42,466 --> 01:03:43,466
Um,

1151
01:03:44,366 --> 01:03:45,633
Mr. Kwon?

1152
01:03:49,400 --> 01:03:50,986
Don't mind too much

1153
01:03:51,066 --> 01:03:52,720
what other people said.

1154
01:03:52,800 --> 01:03:54,553
I won't.

1155
01:03:54,633 --> 01:03:56,153
Because based on today's results,

1156
01:03:56,233 --> 01:03:58,233
anyone would think the same.

1157
01:03:59,133 --> 01:04:00,133
Sure.

1158
01:04:01,166 --> 01:04:03,053
But you know,

1159
01:04:03,133 --> 01:04:06,020
I think you'll win.

1160
01:04:06,100 --> 01:04:07,720
I'll be honest.

1161
01:04:07,800 --> 01:04:09,620
I thought lawyers were people

1162
01:04:09,700 --> 01:04:14,253
who were all about
logic and principles,

1163
01:04:14,333 --> 01:04:17,700
but now I see some lawyers with warm hearts.

1164
01:04:19,000 --> 01:04:20,600
Just like you, Mr. Kwon.

1165
01:04:21,600 --> 01:04:25,486
Because you're warm-hearted and

1166
01:04:25,566 --> 01:04:27,600
considerate, even though
you look like you don't.

1167
01:04:30,200 --> 01:04:33,320
There was a time in the past

1168
01:04:33,400 --> 01:04:35,986
when I felt like I was the
only one left in this world

1169
01:04:36,066 --> 01:04:39,566
and that no one was
there by my side.

1170
01:04:40,533 --> 01:04:43,586
It had been so hard for me.

1171
01:04:43,666 --> 01:04:49,553
Now I'm thinking about
how nice it would've been,

1172
01:04:49,633 --> 01:04:51,786
if I had someone like you

1173
01:04:51,866 --> 01:04:54,053
by my side, back then.

1174
01:04:54,133 --> 01:04:57,220
Because you're that amazing,

1175
01:04:57,300 --> 01:05:00,933
I'm sure you'll solve
this case beautifully.

1176
01:05:25,000 --> 01:05:26,366
It's already...

1177
01:05:33,766 --> 01:05:35,633
Why haven't you gone home already?

1178
01:05:37,633 --> 01:05:40,600
I was searching up some
relevant case examples.

1179
01:05:41,500 --> 01:05:44,853
In case they might help.

1180
01:05:44,933 --> 01:05:46,833
Would you like to
join me for dinner?

1181
01:05:50,100 --> 01:05:52,786
Sure. You know, I'm really hungry.

1182
01:05:52,866 --> 01:05:53,966
Then let's go.

1183
01:06:01,900 --> 01:06:04,620
To be honest,

1184
01:06:04,700 --> 01:06:06,533
I became a lawyer because...

1185
01:06:08,266 --> 01:06:10,086
Rather than to punish people,

1186
01:06:10,166 --> 01:06:12,866
I wanted to be on their side.

1187
01:06:14,533 --> 01:06:15,533
Oh.

1188
01:06:16,966 --> 01:06:18,786
Then why did you say it was

1189
01:06:18,866 --> 01:06:21,566
because lawyers make
lots of money?

1190
01:06:23,200 --> 01:06:27,733
Because... It's kind of
embarrassing to say it honestly.

1191
01:06:28,566 --> 01:06:29,566
Hmmm?

1192
01:06:29,833 --> 01:06:33,633
Then why are you being honest now?

1193
01:06:40,300 --> 01:06:42,886
Because...

1194
01:06:42,966 --> 01:06:46,333
I just wanted to, after
what you told me.

1195
01:06:47,466 --> 01:06:51,766
Thank you for telling me that
you believe in me.

1196
01:06:52,800 --> 01:06:59,853
And... If you
find yourself in that situation,

1197
01:06:59,933 --> 01:07:03,300
where you feel like you have
no one else in this world...

1198
01:07:06,700 --> 01:07:09,400
then I'll be on your side.

1199
01:07:22,633 --> 01:07:23,866
Mr. Kwon...

1200
01:07:36,566 --> 01:07:39,900
There's something
I need to tell you.

1201
01:07:42,366 --> 01:07:43,433
But...

1202
01:07:46,266 --> 01:07:48,053
But not just now.

1203
01:07:48,133 --> 01:07:52,766
However, this feeling...
What I'm feeling now,

1204
01:07:54,800 --> 01:07:59,633
I'm going to tell you someday.

1205
01:08:07,966 --> 01:08:09,033
Ms. Oh Jin-shim.

1206
01:08:17,233 --> 01:08:18,266
Do you...

1207
01:08:19,900 --> 01:08:21,233
...like...

1208
01:08:25,866 --> 01:08:26,866
What?

1209
01:08:27,633 --> 01:08:29,466
(Thank you to Hwang Chan-seong for
his special appearance)

1210
01:08:32,000 --> 01:08:33,800
(It's alright, anytime)

1211
01:09:04,433 --> 01:09:06,066
(Touch Your Heart)

1212
01:09:06,166 --> 01:09:07,286
Working girl,

1213
01:09:07,366 --> 01:09:08,820
workaholic!

1214
01:09:08,900 --> 01:09:10,753
You're so sexy.

1215
01:09:10,833 --> 01:09:12,486
Aren't you slaving
my Yun-seo around?

1216
01:09:12,566 --> 01:09:14,033
"My" Yun-seo?

1217
01:09:14,433 --> 01:09:16,133
- Hey, I...
- "Oppa?"

1218
01:09:16,500 --> 01:09:17,520
Would you like some coffee?

1219
01:09:17,600 --> 01:09:20,453
Didn't he tell me not to
slave you around?

1220
01:09:20,533 --> 01:09:21,620
Your boyfriend, I mean.

1221
01:09:21,700 --> 01:09:23,166
You've never had
a girlfriend, have you?

1222
01:09:23,600 --> 01:09:26,686
Because I don't think you have
talent in that field.

1223
01:09:26,766 --> 01:09:27,953
Someone once told me,

1224
01:09:28,033 --> 01:09:29,353
that she thinks I'll win this case.

1225
01:09:29,433 --> 01:09:31,486
So please believe in me.

1226
01:09:31,566 --> 01:09:33,386
This has taken a new turn.

1227
01:09:33,466 --> 01:09:35,820
This person could be
our only witness,

1228
01:09:35,900 --> 01:09:38,333
or even a whole new suspect.
